.TH intrflush 3
.SH NAME
\*Lintrflush\*O \- Enables a flush on interrupt
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint intrflush(\*Vwin\*L, \*Vbf\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L;
    bool \*Vbf\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "intrflush subroutine"
If \*Lintrflush\*O is enabled, pressing an interrupt key
(interrupt, break, quit) flushes all output in the tty driver queue.
This gives the effect of a faster response to the interrupt
but causes the \*Lcurses\*O program to have an inaccurate
picture of what is on the screen.
Disabling the option prevents the flush.
.PP
The default for the option is dependent on the tty driver settings.
You have to force the terminal into the state you require.
The window argument is ignored.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Lintrflush\*O function returns OK on success and ERR on error.
.EQ
